transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes, I was calling because I wanted to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay. Can I get your phone number please?

Speaker 2: 612-227-2391.

Speaker 1: Okay, I got Carl Morrill in St. Michael, Minnesota.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right, Carl, it does look like you are a VIP member here.

Speaker 2: Are you overstocked on product right now?

Speaker 1: Need to pump some brakes for a while?

Speaker 2: No, I'm not overstocked or anything.

Speaker 1: Not overstocked where the pills are not a fit for you or?

Speaker 2: No, they're not – doesn't seem to be working as I thought they were going to.

Speaker 1: Oh, really? Okay.

Speaker 2: When you take them, you take them on an empty stomach and no alcohol, right?

Speaker 1: Yep. I don't drink at all.

Speaker 2: You don't – not at all. Love it.

Speaker 1: If you are willing to, we are with Pfizer, Carl,

Speaker 2: so we do have multiple variations of the Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: I can send you a sample of one that's made in our France factory that's FDA approved.

Speaker 2: It's a lot more potent.

Speaker 1: Just releasing it recently, actually,

Speaker 2: so I can send you the updated pill completely for free to try.

Speaker 1: If this one gives you the kick that you're looking for, call us back and let us know,

Speaker 2: and we'll talk about your future needs with this one rather than the one that you've been getting.

Speaker 1: Okay. I'd be willing to try that.

Speaker 2: Okay. Sounds good. I'll message the pharmacy right now to send them out.

Speaker 1: It's pretty tricky to determine how soon they'll get there because of the weather right now,

Speaker 2: so just be patient with it.

Speaker 1: I'd expect them by maybe Wednesday or Thursday of next week,

Speaker 2: and these pills will have the number 100 pressed onto them like a stamp.

Speaker 1: That's how you'll be able to identify the difference, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, Carl. Great talking to you. I hope you have a great day, all right?

Speaker 2: Yes. Thank you.

Speaker 1: All right. Take care.

Speaker 2: Yep. Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
